Certainly! Let's take a sample sentence and provide the JSON format for POS tagging along with phrase identification. Then, I'll present a summary table showing the frequency and types of each part of speech, phrase, and clause.

### Sample Sentence:
"The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog."

### JSON Format with POS Tagging and Phrase Identification:

```json
{
  "sentence": "The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog.",
  "tokens": [
    {
      "word": "The",
      "pos": "DT",
      "phrase": "NP"
    },
    {
      "word": "quick",
      "pos": "JJ",
      "phrase": "NP"
    },
    {
      "word": "brown",
      "pos": "JJ",
      "phrase": "NP"
    },
    {
      "word": "fox",
      "pos": "NN",
      "phrase": "NP"
    },
    {
      "word": "jumps",
      "pos": "VBZ",
      "phrase": "VP"
    },
    {
      "word": "over",
      "pos": "IN",
      "phrase": "PP"
    },
    {
      "word": "the",
      "pos": "DT",
      "phrase": "NP"
    },
    {
      "word": "lazy",
      "pos": "JJ",
      "phrase": "NP"
    },
    {
      "word": "dog",
      "pos": "NN",
      "phrase": "NP"
    }
  ],
  "phrases": [
    {
      "type": "Noun Phrase",
      "text": "The quick brown fox"
    },
    {
      "type": "Verb Phrase",
      "text": "jumps"
    },
    {
      "type": "Prepositional Phrase",
      "text": "over the lazy dog"
    },
    {
      "type": "Noun Phrase",
      "text": "the lazy dog"
    }
  ]
}
```

### Summary Table:

| Part of Speech | Frequency | Phrase Type        | Frequency |
|----------------|-----------|--------------------|-----------|
| Determiner (DT)| 2         | Noun Phrase (NP)   | 2         |
| Adjective (JJ) | 3         | Verb Phrase (VP)   | 1         |
| Noun (NN)      | 2         | Prepositional Phrase (PP)| 1    |
| Verb (VBZ)     | 1         |                    |           |
| Preposition (IN)| 1        |                    |           |

This JSON format classifies each word in the sentence by its part of speech and identifies the noun, verb, and prepositional phrases. The summary table provides an overview of the frequency and types of parts of speech and phrases used in the sentence.
